{"id":36163,"title":"[Prenatal diagnosis of and therapy for congenital diaphragmatic hernia].","abstract":"Congenital diaphragmatic hernia is a malformation presenting with varying degrees of severity. An accurate prediction of outcome is crucial for parental counselling and therapeutic planning. In selected cases, foetal endoscopic tracheal occlusion (FETO) can improve foetal outcome. Timely referral to a highly specialised centre is important when the requirement for extracorporeal membrane oxygenation (ECMO) is expected. ","date":"2014-03-05","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24595910","annotations":[{"name":"Extracorporeal membrane oxygenation","weight":0.910027,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extracorporeal_membrane_oxygenation"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.815845,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Prenatal diagnosis","weight":0.808784,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prenatal_diagnosis"},{"name":"Fetus","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fetus"},{"name":"Hernia","weight":0.793943,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hernia"},{"name":"Congenital disorder","weight":0.781843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congenital_disorder"},{"name":"Vertebrate trachea","weight":0.781457,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertebrate_trachea"},{"name":"Endoscopy","weight":0.768171,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endoscopy"},{"name":"Pregnancy","weight":0.720457,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pregnancy"},{"name":"Thoracic diaphragm","weight":0.716901,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thoracic_diaphragm"},{"name":"Extracorporeal","weight":0.70938,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extracorporeal"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.650676,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.